The Campo Project was born from the practical interest of integrating Psychology and Art. This means viewing art critically and sensitively. Make the artistic act significant and existential, praising its process, subjectivity and individual and collective powers. 

The Campo Project is the space in which we operate, in a field where there are no walls, the horizons are extensive and it is possible to contact the surrounding people, cultures and ideas.

Our work is focused on artistic reflections and practices, linked to observation, curiosity and appreciation of subjectivity in the face of artistic practice and its consequences in the creation processes.

Therefore, our project has three pillars of action:

The 3 Integrative Acts of Campo


Art
Visualize art in a sensitive way and find in it senses and meanings that provide self-knowledge, uniqueness, creativity, etc., and add to the individual's existential clinical process;
Practice being an artist: taking art as an expression and using it to your advantage, freely and spontaneously. Having art as a tool to visualize in reality, through works and creations, their internal meanings and symbols;
Share, publicize and bring reflections on art and creation processes.

Psychology
Support clinical and theoretical management to provide creative clinical care;
Share, disseminate and bring reflections on Gestalt Therapy themes and concepts;
Share, publicize and bring reflections on art and creation processes through the eyes of Psychology.

Art therapy
Provide individual and group art therapy clinical care;
Creative clinical camp for consultants interested in starting creative therapy;
Clinical assistance and support for visual artists who wish to observe their existential process + monitor this process linked to their artistic productions. With this, understand your creation process, obstacles, difficulties and potential, awareness of the artistic process, search for meanings and symbols that appear in your aesthetics.

